</taxonomicName>
. So far found only in a limited area on the east slope of the Andes in 
<collectingCountry box="[819,915,1145,1171]" name="Ecuador" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
. Specific locality information on many of these records can be found in 
<bibRefCitation author="Mauffray, W. F." box="[421,611,1181,1207]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" pagination="165 - 170" refId="ref196240" refString="Mauffray, W. F. (1999) Oxyagrion tennesseni spec. nov. from Ecuador (Zygoptera: Coenagrionidae). Odonatologica, 28 (2), 165 - 170." type="journal article" year="1999">Mauffray (1999)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
